\ a definition that fails mid-compile rolls back entirely: no callable stub
: loopy | acc | [: >x | :] ;
loopy

\ compiler state is clean afterward: locals compile and run fine
: fine | a | 3 to a a ;
fine . cr

\ a failing load caught by catch rolls back too
": broken | q | [: >z | :] ;" "/tmp/w124_bad.h2o" write-file
[: "/tmp/w124_bad.h2o" load :] catch . cr . cr
broken

\ a definition spanning lines is abandoned by an error on a later line
: partial
nosuchword
partial
